CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 9, 1961, pg. 10, reads: "SOME CABBAGE! - Thomas Hollis, employe [employee] of Mrs. Robert L. Vann, president and treasurer of The Pittsburgh Courier, displays a prize cabbage of about 18 pounds which he grew in a garden of the Vann estate in Oakmont. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Thomas Hollis wearing pith helmet and squatting beside large prizewinning cabbage, in garden with corn and other vegetables on estate of Jessie Vann, Oakmont
